text: Dyurtyuli () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Kurmankeyevsky Selsoviet, Davlekanovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 317 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 14 km from Davlekanovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Davlekanovsky District
title: Dyurtyuli, Davlekanovsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
